articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Ukrainian forces have for the first time hit a latest-generation Russian Sukhoi Su-57 fighter jet at an air base inside Russia, Kyiv's GUR defence intelligence agency said on Sunday, showing satellite pictures which it said confirmed the strike.
articles.title: Ukraine says latest-generation Russian fighter jet hit for first time

articles.author: Jeff Mason
articles.description: The White House declined to say on Sunday whether President Joe Biden will meet Benjamin Netanyahu when the Israeli prime minister visits Washington next month to address the U.S. Congress.
articles.title: No word from White House on whether Biden to meet Netanyahu in Washington

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: British TV presenter and healthy living advocate Michael Mosley has been found dead on the Greek island of Symi, a deputy mayor of the island told Reuters on Sunday.
articles.title: British TV presenter Mosley found dead on Greek island of Symi - local official

articles.author: Philip Blenkinsop
articles.description: Voters in 21 EU countries including France and Germany will conclude a four-day election for the European Parliament on Sunday, which is expected to shift the assembly to the right and boost the numbers of eurosceptic nationalists.
articles.title: European Parliament poised for rightward shift after final voting

articles.author: Jack Kim
articles.description: North Korea has resumed sending balloons carrying trash over the border to South Korea, officials and news reports said on Sunday, a week after it vowed to continue if anti-North Korea leaflets are flown from the South.
articles.title: North Korea resumes sending trash balloons to South Korea

articles.author: Jack Kim
articles.description: South Korea's main doctors' lobby group said on Sunday it would go on strike on June 18 to protest the government's healthcare reform plan, defying a warning by the prime minister that such action would damage the credibility of the medical community.
articles.title: South Korea's doctors plan June 18 strike to protest reforms

articles.author: Stoyan Nenov
articles.description: Bulgarians head to the polls on Sunday for their sixth parliamentary election in three years, but analysts say the vote is unlikely to yield a stable government that can end prolonged political instability and unblock economic reforms.
articles.title: Bulgaria holds another snap election, with more instability seen ahead

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A majority of Thais are dissatisfied with the government of Prime Minister Srettha Thavisin, who took office nine months ago, as it has not been able to resolve the country's problems and implement policies, an opinion poll showed on Sunday.
articles.title: Majority of Thais unhappy with PM Srettha's government, poll shows

articles.author: Jeff Mason
articles.description: U.S. President Joe Biden and his wife, Jill Biden, will conclude their trip to France on Sunday with a stop at an American cemetery that former president Donald Trump declined to visit in 2018, drawing widespread criticism.
articles.title: Biden to visit American cemetery in France that Trump skipped

articles.author: Nathan Layne
articles.description: Republican presidential candidate Donald Trump will hold an outdoor rally in sweltering Las Vegas, Nevada, on Sunday, seeking to shore up support in a swing state he lost twice but which polls suggest is leaning his way in the Nov. 5 election.
articles.title: Trump to hold rally in swing state Nevada during heatwave
